que I'bellezza empiora ♪</i>

03:46.239 --> 03:48.173
<i>♪ Ella fuggevole ♪</i>

03:48.241 --> 03:50.801
<i>♪ Fuggevole ora ♪</i>

03:50.911 --> 03:53.971
<i>♪ Sin abbreviato lutta ♪</i>

03:54.080 --> 03:56.139
<i>♪ L 'biamo ni docci
appremiti... ♪</i>

03:56.249 --> 03:57.580
Dave,

03:57.651 --> 03:59.050
is Moocher home?

03:59.119 --> 04:01.178
<i>♪ Le amore ♪</i>

04:01.288 --> 04:04.121
<i>♪ Que quelle
I'occhio accore ♪</i>

04:04.190 --> 04:09.628
<i>♪ Ominipotante va ♪</i>

04:09.696 --> 04:13.860
<i>♪ L 'biamo,
amore, amore ♪</i>

04:13.934 --> 04:15.424
<i>Hey, ciao, Bambini.</i>

04:15.502 --> 04:17.298
<i>♪ Puccali bocci
del abra ♪</i>

04:17.370 --> 04:18.803
<i>Buon giorno!</i>

04:18.872 --> 04:22.308
<i>♪ Ha ha,
n'esco praildi ♪</i>

04:22.375 --> 04:25.833
<i>♪ Ha ha,
n'esco praildi ♪</i>

04:25.946 --> 04:28.574
<i>♪ N'fasi ♪ ♪</i>

04:28.682 --> 04:31.651
He was as normal
as pumpkin pie,

04:31.718 --> 04:35.210
and now look at him.

04:35.322 --> 04:37.688
His poor parents.

04:39.693 --> 04:41.661
It's that cologne
he wears.

04:41.761 --> 04:43.991
It's called...

04:44.064 --> 04:46.032
Neapolitan
Sunset.

04:46.099 --> 04:49.034
Yeah? Well, the flies
seem to like it.

04:49.102 --> 04:50.535
There.

04:53.607 --> 04:55.541
This is it?

04:55.609 --> 04:58.544
Well, you know what
the doctor said.

04:58.612 --> 05:00.045
At your age...

05:00.113 --> 05:03.480
What the hell
do you mean "at my age"?

05:03.550 --> 05:05.484
Damn see-through coffee.

05:05.552 --> 05:07.986
He says you have
a bad heart.

05:08.054 --> 05:10.488
That's got nothing
to do with my age.

05:10.557 --> 05:12.491
Our son's
ruining my health, Evelyn.

05:12.559 --> 05:14.493
What's he going to do?

05:14.561 --> 05:18.497
He wanted a year off,
so I give him a year.

05:18.565 --> 05:20.499
It hasn't
been a year yet.

05:20.567 --> 05:25.004
But, Evelyn, look what's happened
to him. He's turned into an "Ity."

05:25.071 --> 05:28.507
"Ciao, Papa. Ciao, mama.
'Arrivederci. '"

05:28.575 --> 05:30.008
That's "Ity" talk.

05:30.076 --> 05:33.011
I used to think
it was funny at first.

05:33.079 --> 05:34.512
Not funny anymore.

05:34.581 --> 05:36.515
He was very sickly

05:36.583 --> 05:39.518
until he started riding
around on that bike.

05:39.586 --> 05:44.148
Well, now his body's fine,
but his mind is going.

05:44.257 --> 05:46.521
He used to be
a smart kid.

05:46.593 --> 05:49.824
I thought he'd
go to college.

05:49.896 --> 05:52.160
You didn't want him to.

05:52.232 --> 05:54.530
Why should he?
I never went.

05:54.601 --> 05:58.002
At 19, I worked
in the quarry ten hours a day.

05:58.071 --> 06:00.938
Most of the quarries
have closed.

06:01.007 --> 06:03.237
Let him find
another job.

06:03.309 --> 06:05.777
Jobs are not
that easy to find.

06:05.879 --> 06:08.109
Let him look at least.

06:08.181 --> 06:10.411
Let him come home
tired from looking.

06:10.483 --> 06:11.916
He's never tired.

06:11.985 --> 06:13.418
He's never
miserable.

06:13.486 --> 06:14.544
He's young.

06:14.621 --> 06:18.421
When I was young,
I was tired and miserable.

06:18.491 --> 06:21.927
I had
my own place at 17.

06:21.995 --> 06:25.362
He says Italian families
stay together.

06:25.432 --> 06:27.900
Evelyn,
we are not Italian.

06:28.001 --> 06:29.935
I know, I know.

06:30.003 --> 06:34.440
It's just that I come
from a big family myself,

06:34.507 --> 06:37.442
and it was
kind of nice.

06:37.510 --> 06:40.946
He thinks we should
have another child.

06:41.014 --> 06:41.946
What?

06:44.417 --> 06:45.907
<i>Buon giorno,
Papa.</i>

06:46.019 --> 06:48.453
I'm not Papa!
I'm your damn father!

06:48.521 --> 06:49.954
<i>Buon giorno,
Mama.</i>

06:50.023 --> 06:51.650
She's your damn mother.

06:51.758 --> 06:53.749
Did you win again?

06:53.860 --> 06:56.420
The victory,
she was easy,

06:56.529 --> 06:58.463
but the promoter
tells me

06:58.531 --> 07:01.967
that the Italians
will be here soon.

07:02.035 --> 07:05.402
<i>I will race
with the best... Italianos.</i>

07:05.472 --> 07:07.406
Like nightingales
they sing.

07:07.474 --> 07:09.408
Like eagles
they fly.

07:09.476 --> 07:12.912
Speaking of flies,
you brought some in.

07:12.979 --> 07:15.413
<i>Fly in Italian
is mosca.</i>

07:15.482 --> 07:16.915
In English
it's "pest."

07:16.983 --> 07:18.416
Speaking of pests...

07:18.485 --> 07:20.919
Isn't this
a lovely trophy?

07:20.987 --> 07:22.420
Oh, yeah.

07:22.489 --> 07:24.423
So what?

07:24.491 --> 07:28.427
I lived 50 years,
I never got a trophy.

07:28.495 --> 07:30.429
You never
got a trophy?

07:30.497 --> 07:31.930
Nope, never got one.

07:31.998 --> 07:33.431
I give you this,

07:33.500 --> 07:34.933
numero uno,
King Papa.

07:35.001 --> 07:36.434
Don't do that.

07:36.503 --> 07:38.664
I have to take
a shower.

07:48.448 --> 07:50.177
<i>[Figaro Playing]</i>

07:53.019 --> 07:55.453
There's that
"Ity" music again!

07:55.522 --> 07:58.457
I'm having this
out with him now!

08:03.363 --> 08:05.422
<i>♪ Abra m'figaro,
abra m'figaro ♪</i>

08:05.532 --> 08:07.796
<i>♪ Abra bellissimo,
hatte fortuna ♪</i>

08:07.867 --> 08:10.859
<i>♪ Hatte fortuna, hatte
fortuna Leone cara... ♪</i>

08:19.479 --> 08:21.413
What's the matter?

08:21.481 --> 08:22.914
He's shaving.

08:22.982 --> 08:24.415
Well, so what?

08:24.484 --> 08:25.917
His legs.

08:25.985 --> 08:28.215
He's shaving
his legs.

08:28.288 --> 08:30.449
<i>♪ Figaro ♪</i>

08:30.557 --> 08:31.489
<i>♪ Fi ♪</i>

08:31.558 --> 08:33.287
<i>♪ Garo ♪</i>

08:33.359 --> 08:36.726
<i>♪ Figaro, figaro,
figaro, figaro ♪ ♪</i>

08:47.307 --> 08:48.239
Yoo-hoo.

08:48.308 --> 08:49.240
Nancy!

08:49.309 --> 08:53.370
I was just
on my way to work.

08:53.479 --> 08:54.912
Come on in.

08:59.485 --> 09:00.918
You know what?

09:00.987 --> 09:02.352
No. What?

09:02.422 --> 09:03.855
I'm leaving home,
that's what.

09:03.923 --> 09:05.857
Where are you going?

09:05.925 --> 09:07.859
About
five blocks south.

09:07.927 --> 09:09.360
Oh.

09:09.429 --> 09:12.364
I found this nice
little place to rent.

09:12.432 --> 09:14.366
It's so cute
I could scream.

09:14.434 --> 09:18.871
My folks said I could have
some of their furniture.

09:18.938 --> 09:20.371
All right!

09:28.448 --> 09:32.384
Maybe you could
give me a hand... moving.

09:35.955 --> 09:37.388
Oh, sure.

09:37.457 --> 09:40.893
If I'm not too busy,
you know?

09:48.334 --> 09:49.858
How's the job?

09:49.969 --> 09:51.903
You know what?

09:51.971 --> 09:54.064
Frank said if I keep up
the good work,

09:54.173 --> 09:57.233
in time, I'll become
head cashier.

09:57.343 --> 09:58.537
That's great.

10:01.481 --> 10:04.416
Well,
I should go now.

10:04.484 --> 10:05.917
Nancy.

10:05.985 --> 10:07.418
Uh...

10:07.487 --> 10:10.923
I think
I'll walk you to work.

10:10.990 --> 10:13.925
I'm going out
that way anyways.

10:23.970 --> 10:27.770
It gets 30 miles
to the gallon.

10:27.874 --> 10:32.277
Of course, the mileage
you get may vary.

10:32.345 --> 10:34.279
It's a beaut, right?

10:35.348 --> 10:36.610
Right.

10:37.884 --> 10:40.512
Boy, you sure know how
to pick 'em.

10:40.586 --> 10:43.612
Frankly, this is
the best car on the lot.

10:43.690 --> 10:44.952
Quality product.

10:45.058 --> 10:46.423
<i>Buon giorno,
Papa!</i>

10:46.526 --> 10:47.424
<i>Come sta?</i>

10:54.367 --> 10:56.232
Friend of yours?

11:01.708 --> 11:04.939
Aren't you glad
we got fired from the A & P?

11:07.046 --> 11:10.413
I mean, right now,
we'd be working.

11:10.483 --> 11:12.917
We didn't
get fired, Mike.

11:13.019 --> 11:14.919
You got fired.
We quit.

11:15.021 --> 11:17.251
All for one
and one for all.

11:17.357 --> 11:19.291
You know, there
ain't many places

11:19.359 --> 11:23.420
that will hire
all four of us.

11:23.496 --> 11:28.433
- You know what I'd like to be?
- Smart.

11:28.501 --> 11:30.935
A cartoon
of some kind.

11:31.037 --> 11:32.937
Wouldn't that
be great?

11:33.039 --> 11:35.940
You know,
when they get hit on the head

11:36.042 --> 11:37.441
with a frying pan

11:37.510 --> 11:39.944
and their head looks like
the frying pan

11:40.046 --> 11:41.946
with the handle
and everything?

11:42.048 --> 11:43.948
Then they
go booooing!

11:44.050 --> 11:45.950
Their head comes
back to normal.

11:46.052 --> 11:47.952
Wouldn't that
be great?

11:50.056 --> 11:53.457
How did you get to be
so stupid, Cyril?

11:53.526 --> 11:57.963
I don't know.
Guess I have a dumb heredity.

11:58.064 --> 11:59.964
What's your
excuse, Michael?

12:10.343 --> 12:12.243
You hear from
your folks, Mooch?

12:12.345 --> 12:13.744
Yeah, my dad called.

12:13.813 --> 12:16.748
There's a lot
more jobs in Chicago.

12:16.816 --> 12:19.944
He hasn't gotten
anything yet, though.

12:21.888 --> 12:24.721
Wanted to know
if the house was sold.

12:24.791 --> 12:28.557
He could use the money
something fierce.

12:30.363 --> 12:32.388
You can come live with me
when it's sold.

12:32.465 --> 12:34.899
In Italy, everybody
lives together.

12:35.001 --> 12:37.902
Since you won
that Italian bike, man,

12:38.004 --> 12:39.904
you've been
acting weird.

12:40.006 --> 12:43.407
You're really getting
to think you're Italian.

12:43.476 --> 12:46.206
I wouldn't mind thinking
I was somebody myself.

12:51.017 --> 12:54.680
I think the door's stuck
on that icebox.

13:04.163 --> 13:05.790
I can't see him!

13:05.865 --> 13:07.298
Oh, yoo-hoo!

13:07.400 --> 13:10.927
It's got
no back on it.

13:28.588 --> 13:31.022
What the hell
are they doing here?

13:43.436 --> 13:46.599
I've never seen anybody
dive off from up there.

13:46.706 --> 13:50.164
Hey, you bastards!

13:50.276 --> 13:51.243
Who's that?

13:51.344 --> 13:52.971
Hey, cutters!

13:53.079 --> 13:55.445
They got indoor
and outdoor pools on campus,

13:55.515 --> 13:57.278
and they got
to come here.

13:57.350 --> 13:58.977
It's my
goddamn quarry.

13:59.085 --> 14:01.178
This hole,

14:01.287 --> 14:04.017
this quarry hole
is mine!

14:04.090 --> 14:05.387
Hey, screw you, Cyril.

14:05.458 --> 14:07.551
Come on, let's
get out of here.

14:07.627 --> 14:09.561
If they
can come here,

14:09.629 --> 14:11.426
then we'll go
to their campus.

14:45.498 --> 14:46.931
Going to college

14:47.033 --> 14:49.934
must do something
to girls' tits, I swear.

14:50.036 --> 14:51.901
Just look at 'em.

14:53.339 --> 14:55.068
Hi there!

14:55.141 --> 14:56.972
What's your major?

15:02.315 --> 15:06.376
Sure look like
they've got it made.

15:06.485 --> 15:08.510
That's because
they're rich.

15:08.588 --> 15:11.216
Italians are poor,
but they're happy.

15:11.324 --> 15:14.589
Yeah, maybe
in Italy.

15:14.694 --> 15:15.592
Whoa! Whoo!

15:15.695 --> 15:16.719
Hey, good one.

15:16.796 --> 15:17.728
Go!

15:17.797 --> 15:19.731
All right! Here.

15:19.799 --> 15:22.927
I wonder what it's like
to kiss a coed.

15:26.606 --> 15:27.766
[Tires Screech]

15:27.873 --> 15:29.898
Ha ha ha ha ha!

15:29.976 --> 15:31.568
[Student]
Come on!

15:31.644 --> 15:33.942
Hey, that bastard's
giving us the finger.

15:34.013 --> 15:36.413
Hey, we're on
their turf, Mike.

15:38.384 --> 15:39.976
Come on!

15:40.086 --> 15:41.246
Dumb-ass
cutters!

15:41.354 --> 15:47.384
Goddamn bastard-lickin'
retards!

15:47.460 --> 15:48.927
Number 1, move!

15:50.663 --> 15:53.154
Hut! 18! Hut!

15:55.901 --> 15:57.835
[Whistle Blows]

16:03.576 --> 16:07.569
I thought I was a great
quarterback in high school.

16:07.647 --> 16:09.080
Still think so, too.

16:09.148 --> 16:12.083
Can't even bring myself
to light a cigarette

16:12.151 --> 16:15.416
because I keep thinking
I got to stay in shape.

16:23.663 --> 16:25.563
Know what really gets me?

16:25.665 --> 16:28.566
I got to live in
this stinking town,

16:28.668 --> 16:31.068
and I got to read
in the newspapers

16:31.137 --> 16:32.570
about some hotshot kid,

16:32.672 --> 16:35.197
new star
of the college team.

16:36.676 --> 16:40.737
Every year it's going
to be a new one...

16:42.048 --> 16:45.449
and every year, it's
never going to be me.

16:46.519 --> 16:48.384
I'm just going
to be Mike.

16:50.189 --> 16:51.850
20-year-old Mike.

16:53.626 --> 16:55.253
30-year-old Mike.

16:56.529 --> 16:58.827
Old mean old man Mike.

17:02.968 --> 17:06.404
These college kids will
never get old or out of shape

17:06.472 --> 17:09.737
'cause new ones
come along every year.

17:12.478 --> 17:15.970
They're going
to keep calling us cutters.

17:17.983 --> 17:20.416
To them, it's just
a dirty word.

17:20.486 --> 17:24.252
To me, it's just
something else

17:24.357 --> 17:26.916
I never got
a chance to be.

17:34.367 --> 17:36.267
<i>Quanto serra il pro-</i>

17:36.369 --> 17:40.499
<i>pro-pros-prossimo.</i>

17:51.417 --> 17:54.284
<i>Mama Mia!</i>

18:04.397 --> 18:06.297
[Horn Honks]

18:55.581 --> 18:57.640
<i>Signorina!</i>

19:14.767 --> 19:16.234
<i>Signorina!</i>

19:17.937 --> 19:20.371
<i>Signorina!</i>

19:20.473 --> 19:21.531
<i>Signorina...</i>

19:22.675 --> 19:24.540
<i>signorina...</i>

19:24.610 --> 19:26.043
you, uh...

19:27.480 --> 19:28.879
is yours, no?

19:30.149 --> 19:32.709
You mean you've
been chasing me with this?

19:32.785 --> 19:34.047
Is nothing.

19:34.119 --> 19:35.677
<i>Niente, signorina.</i>

19:36.956 --> 19:39.550
Are you
an exchange student or something?

19:41.427 --> 19:42.860
<i>Si.</i>

19:42.962 --> 19:44.361
<i>I am
Italiano.</i>

19:44.430 --> 19:46.864
My name is
Enrico Gimondi.

19:48.267 --> 19:50.701
My name is
Katherine Bennett.

19:50.803 --> 19:52.498
Ah, Catherina.

19:52.605 --> 19:54.698
Catherina.

19:56.442 --> 19:57.875
Well, thanks again...

19:57.977 --> 19:59.376
again.

19:59.445 --> 20:00.878
Bye.

20:02.982 --> 20:05.075
Ciao.

20:45.357 --> 20:46.289
[Pop, Hiss]

20:46.358 --> 20:48.189
Son of a bitch!

20:55.034 --> 20:58.333
All right,
keep it steady!

20:58.404 --> 21:00.065
Keep your elbows bent!

21:00.139 --> 21:02.073
That's... that's right!

21:02.141 --> 21:04.666
Pick it up,
Kath... 30!

21:11.216 --> 21:12.148
Hi.

21:12.217 --> 21:13.912
What are you
doing, Kathy?

21:13.986 --> 21:14.975
Goddamn it!

21:18.857 --> 21:21.155
I want an answer, Evelyn.

21:21.226 --> 21:23.660
What are we
going to do about him?

21:23.729 --> 21:25.663
I don't know, dear.

21:25.731 --> 21:28.598
We could strangle him
while he's asleep.

21:28.701 --> 21:30.168
That's not funny,
Evelyn.

21:30.235 --> 21:31.827
Talk to him.

21:31.904 --> 21:35.931
I'm afraid to talk to him.
I'm afraid to look at him.

21:36.008 --> 21:40.172
I'm afraid his eyes
would twirl like pinwheels.

21:40.245 --> 21:41.678
I'm only
giving you these

21:41.747 --> 21:43.977
because you promised
to calm down.

21:44.083 --> 21:45.914
Don't expect
any more.

21:47.086 --> 21:51.887
<i>♪ Amor Alma ♪</i>

21:51.991 --> 21:54.391
I can't eat
with that noise on.

21:55.728 --> 22:04.898
<i>♪ Si mourto apprezzi ♪</i>

22:05.004 --> 22:06.562
<i>♪ L 'bello... ♪</i>

22:09.008 --> 22:11.568
Evelyn, he's not
even in his room.

22:13.912 --> 22:15.106
Stop!

22:15.214 --> 22:19.810
What the hell are you doing?
Them's my French fries!

22:19.918 --> 22:21.351
Oh, Mama!

22:21.420 --> 22:23.389
Evelyn!

22:23.522 --> 22:25.820
Oh, my God,
what's the matter?

22:25.891 --> 22:28.826
<i>Mio cuore.
My heart.</i>

22:28.894 --> 22:30.327
Oh, my heart!

22:30.396 --> 22:32.830
It's these damn
French fries.

22:32.898 --> 22:35.332
Hey, they're
my damn French fries.

22:35.401 --> 22:40.236
I have such
a pain in my heart, Mama, Papa.

22:41.407 --> 22:43.841
I'm in love.

22:45.944 --> 22:47.969
<i>[Music Playing]</i>

22:50.082 --> 22:53.518
Suzy says this guy
sent you flowers.

22:53.585 --> 22:57.021
So what?
You never sent me flowers.

22:57.089 --> 22:59.023
Who is he, Kath?

22:59.091 --> 23:01.525
Some crazy guy I met.

23:01.593 --> 23:04.824
God, what's
gotten into you?

23:12.271 --> 23:13.568
<i>Buon giorno.</i>

23:20.979 --> 23:22.071
Mama!

23:22.147 --> 23:23.239
Mama!

23:23.315 --> 23:25.442
Mama,
the Italians are coming!

23:25.517 --> 23:27.747
They're coming to race
in Indianapolis!

23:27.820 --> 23:29.583
The team Cinzano!

23:29.655 --> 23:33.489
<i>Oh, grazie, Dona
do Santa Maria.</i>

23:33.559 --> 23:36.494
Oh, Dave, try not
to become Catholic on us.

23:55.948 --> 23:58.007
<i>Grazie, signore.</i>

23:58.083 --> 23:59.573
<i>Molto grazie!</i>

26:17.990 --> 26:19.924
Faster.

27:20.018 --> 27:22.646
[Siren]

27:31.697 --> 27:32.755
Damn!

28:10.469 --> 28:11.401
Ahh.

28:19.311 --> 28:22.246
Ah, there you are,
Fellini.

28:22.314 --> 28:23.747
<i>Come sta, eh?</i>

28:25.484 --> 28:27.952
Are you hungry?

28:28.020 --> 28:31.456
This is spicy
meatballs here.

28:36.828 --> 28:38.921
Mmm!

28:38.997 --> 28:42.091
[Slurps]

28:42.167 --> 28:44.260
<i>Mangiare, eh?</i>

28:50.509 --> 28:52.909
Hey, hey!

28:52.978 --> 28:55.173
Guess what.
The Italians are coming.

28:55.247 --> 28:56.771
Guess what.
Mooch is going.

28:56.848 --> 28:58.679
You've got
to talk to him.

28:58.750 --> 29:00.240
Where're you
going, Mooch?

29:00.318 --> 29:02.047
He's getting a job.

29:02.120 --> 29:03.212
So?

29:03.288 --> 29:05.449
So? He's getting a job!

29:09.795 --> 29:11.729
[Mike]
Campus street car wash.

29:11.797 --> 29:14.231
Going to wait
on college boys.

29:14.299 --> 29:17.735
Don't forget to smile
now if you want a tip.

29:17.803 --> 29:21.000
I thought we were going
to stick together, man.

29:21.106 --> 29:22.733
I need a job, Mike.

29:22.808 --> 29:23.900
Don't go, Mooch.

29:23.975 --> 29:26.739
They only let you out
on weekends and holidays.

29:26.812 --> 29:28.211
See you later, Cyril.

29:28.280 --> 29:31.443
Hey, don't forget
to write.

29:32.651 --> 29:33.583
Hey.

29:33.652 --> 29:34.914
Take it easy.

29:34.986 --> 29:36.010
Ciao.

29:44.496 --> 29:45.758
You're a little late,

29:45.831 --> 29:48.595
but I guess you won't
let that happen again.

29:48.667 --> 29:49.759
Sorry.

29:49.835 --> 29:51.427
Here's your
sponge and rag,

29:51.503 --> 29:52.765
and there's your place.

29:52.838 --> 29:55.602
And don't forget
to punch the clock, shorty.

30:00.345 --> 30:01.277
All right!

30:01.346 --> 30:02.404
Bravo!

30:02.481 --> 30:03.778
[Whistling]

30:03.849 --> 30:04.781
Yeah!

30:04.850 --> 30:06.112
Whoo!

30:06.184 --> 30:07.879
Way to go, Mooch!

30:16.328 --> 30:18.626
You know, them college boys
ain't so smart.

30:18.697 --> 30:23.634
I sold one of my worst cars
to one of them today.

30:23.702 --> 30:26.000
They ain't
too smart.

30:26.071 --> 30:28.904
It's a good thing
that Dave never...

30:30.942 --> 30:32.409
What is this?

30:33.478 --> 30:34.410
It's, um...

30:34.479 --> 30:36.845
sauteed zucchini.

30:36.915 --> 30:38.348
It's "Ity" food.

30:38.416 --> 30:40.816
I don't want
no "Ity" food.

30:40.886 --> 30:41.910
It's not.

30:41.987 --> 30:44.751
I got it at the A & P.

30:44.823 --> 30:46.688
It's like, uh... squash.

30:46.758 --> 30:49.625
I know "Ity" food
when I hear it.

30:49.694 --> 30:51.628
It's all them
"ini" foods...

30:51.696 --> 30:54.164
Zucchini and linguini
and fettuccine.

30:54.232 --> 30:56.564
I want some
American food, damn it!

30:56.635 --> 30:58.068
I want
French fries!

30:58.136 --> 30:59.262
[Meow]

30:59.337 --> 31:01.862
Oh, get off the table,
Fellini!

31:01.940 --> 31:03.066
That's my cat!

31:03.141 --> 31:05.075
His name is Jake,
not Fellini.

31:05.143 --> 31:07.577
I won't have any "ini"
in this house!

31:07.646 --> 31:09.944
Your name is Jake,
you understand?

31:10.015 --> 31:11.243
[Meow]

31:18.657 --> 31:21.592
Your parents asking
what you're going to do?

31:21.660 --> 31:23.594
I think they're
getting curious.

31:23.662 --> 31:26.597
I sure miss
playing basketball.

31:26.665 --> 31:28.599
I got depressed as hell

31:28.667 --> 31:31.602
when my athlete's foot
and jock itch went away.

31:31.670 --> 31:35.436
So why did you
give it up?

31:35.507 --> 31:37.839
Oh, I don't know.

31:39.344 --> 31:40.606
Ah...

31:40.679 --> 31:43.614
I was sure I was going
to get that scholarship.

31:43.682 --> 31:46.617
My dad, of course,
was sure that I wouldn't.

31:46.685 --> 31:49.119
When I didn't, he was
really understanding, you know?

31:49.187 --> 31:52.122
He loves
to be understanding when I fail.

31:52.190 --> 31:55.125
"That's O.K., Cyril.
I understand."

31:55.193 --> 31:57.627
He even bought me
that guitar

31:57.696 --> 32:00.631
'cause he was sure
I'd never learn to play it.

32:00.699 --> 32:03.566
I'm supposed to take
this college entrance exam.

32:03.635 --> 32:05.068
You're going
to college?

32:05.136 --> 32:06.068
Hell, no!

32:06.137 --> 32:10.073
I just want to see
if I can pass.

32:10.141 --> 32:11.073
Huh.

32:11.142 --> 32:13.576
Maybe I'll take it, too,
and flunk it.

32:13.645 --> 32:16.170
My dad's birthday's
coming up.

32:17.882 --> 32:20.817
Hey, now, look at this.

32:20.885 --> 32:24.184
That's the place
to be right there... Wyoming.

32:24.289 --> 32:28.157
Nothing but prairies and
mountains and nobody around.

32:28.226 --> 32:31.593
All you need
is a bedroll and a good horse.

32:31.663 --> 32:33.096
Don't forget
your toothbrush.

32:33.164 --> 32:35.598
You're still in
your cavity-prone years.

32:38.169 --> 32:39.830
Hey, here's your brother.

32:46.678 --> 32:51.980
I, uh, hear you've been
hot-rodding around campus again.

32:52.050 --> 32:53.483
I wasn't
hot-rodding.

32:53.551 --> 32:56.486
I'm going to have
to take the car back

32:56.554 --> 32:58.317
if you keep it up.

32:59.991 --> 33:00.923
All right.

33:04.162 --> 33:05.857
All right,
all right, all right.

33:05.930 --> 33:06.862
All right.

33:06.931 --> 33:09.365
How you doing, guys?

33:09.434 --> 33:11.231
Well, we're
a little disturbed

33:11.336 --> 33:13.429
by developments
in the Middle East,

33:13.505 --> 33:14.767
but other than that...

33:14.839 --> 33:15.931
Pussy cop.

33:18.343 --> 33:20.573
Hey, I know
what let's do.

33:20.645 --> 33:22.579
Let's drive
to Terre Haute tomorrow.

33:22.647 --> 33:25.081
We ain't been
out of this B-town

33:25.150 --> 33:27.084
in God knows
how long.

33:27.152 --> 33:29.586
That sounds
like a good idea.

33:29.654 --> 33:30.586
I'm, uh...

33:32.157 --> 33:33.886
I'm kind of
busy tomorrow.

33:33.958 --> 33:35.585
Yeah,
that's right.

33:35.660 --> 33:38.629
I'm kind of busy
myself tomorrow.

33:41.599 --> 33:44.762
Well, I just might
go myself, then.

33:47.539 --> 33:50.474
[Italian Music Playing]

33:55.880 --> 33:59.816
<i>♪ Ah ah, la da ♪ ♪</i>

34:01.986 --> 34:05.945
[Guitar Notes Playing]

34:18.168 --> 34:19.431
That's it.

34:19.504 --> 34:21.438
Cyril, that's it.
I recognize it.

34:21.505 --> 34:22.495
Damn right.

34:22.574 --> 34:26.271
But you got to play it
much louder, O.K.?

34:26.311 --> 34:27.277
Don't worry.

34:27.344 --> 34:29.279
I'll make
this catgut meow.

34:29.347 --> 34:32.783
[Strums Loud Chord]

34:33.717 --> 34:36.983
<i>♪ Ha ha ha ♪ ♪</i>

34:37.054 --> 34:38.612
Come on,
just slow down.

34:38.723 --> 34:40.748
Watch out
for the hole! Ow!

34:46.231 --> 34:48.290
How about a little music?

34:54.739 --> 34:55.899
Catherina!

34:57.242 --> 34:58.675
Catherina!

35:05.350 --> 35:06.749
Catherina!

35:22.233 --> 35:25.361
<i>♪ M'appari ♪</i>

35:25.470 --> 35:28.462
<i>♪ Tutt' amor ♪</i>

35:28.573 --> 35:30.006
<i>♪ II mio ♪</i>

35:30.074 --> 35:31.371
<i>♪ Sguardo ♪</i>

35:31.443 --> 35:35.277
<i>♪ L 'incontro ♪</i>

35:35.346 --> 35:38.281
<i>♪ Bella si ♪</i>

35:38.349 --> 35:41.284
<i>♪ Che il mio cor ♪</i>

35:41.352 --> 35:42.876
<i>♪ Ansio ♪</i>

35:42.987 --> 35:43.954
Play it, Cyril!

35:44.022 --> 35:46.582
<i>♪ So a lei volo ♪</i>

35:46.691 --> 35:48.090
<i>♪ Mi feri ♪</i>

35:48.159 --> 35:49.786
<i>♪ M'invaghi ♪</i>

35:49.894 --> 35:52.385
<i>♪ Quell'Angelica
belta ♪</i>

35:52.497 --> 35:54.658
<i>♪ Sculta in cor ♪</i>

35:54.766 --> 35:58.634
<i>♪ Dall'amor
cancellarsi non porta ♪</i>

35:58.703 --> 36:01.638
<i>♪ II pensier di poter ♪</i>

36:01.706 --> 36:04.106
<i>♪ Palpitar con lei d'amor ♪</i>

36:04.175 --> 36:07.269
<i>♪ Puo sopir il martir ♪</i>

36:07.378 --> 36:09.175
<i>♪ Che m'affan ♪</i>

36:09.247 --> 36:12.114
<i>♪ Na e strazia il cor ♪</i>

36:12.183 --> 36:18.588
<i>♪ E strazia il cor ♪</i>

36:18.690 --> 36:22.592
<i>♪ M'appari ♪</i>

36:22.660 --> 36:25.652
<i>♪ Tutt'amor ♪</i>

36:25.763 --> 36:27.594
<i>♪ II mio ♪</i>

36:27.665 --> 36:29.223
<i>♪ Sguardo ♪</i>

36:29.334 --> 36:30.824
<i>♪ L 'incontro ♪</i>

36:30.935 --> 36:32.266
Oh, hi, Rod.

36:32.337 --> 36:33.770
I was just wondering

36:33.838 --> 36:38.104
if you knew there was a guy
over here serenading Kath.

36:38.176 --> 36:43.011
<i>♪ Ansioso a lei volo ♪</i>

36:43.081 --> 36:45.879
<i>♪ Marta, Marta ♪</i>

36:45.950 --> 36:49.317
<i>♪ Tu sparisti ♪</i>

36:49.387 --> 36:51.787
<i>♪ E il mio cor ♪</i>

36:51.856 --> 36:54.848
<i>♪ Cor tuo n'ando ♪</i>

36:54.959 --> 36:57.018
<i>♪ Tu la ♪</i>

36:57.128 --> 36:58.595
<i>♪ Pace ♪</i>

36:58.663 --> 37:01.598
<i>♪ Mi rapisti ♪</i>

37:01.666 --> 37:03.964
<i>♪ Do dolor ♪</i>

37:04.035 --> 37:08.472
<i>♪ Io moriro ♪</i>

37:08.573 --> 37:10.040
<i>♪ Ah ♪</i>

37:10.141 --> 37:12.439
<i>♪ Di dolor morro ♪</i>

37:12.477 --> 37:15.378
<i>♪ Si ♪</i>

37:15.446 --> 37:20.406
<i>♪ Morro ♪ ♪</i>

37:38.102 --> 37:41.230
Good night
and thank you!

37:42.473 --> 37:43.963
Whoa!

37:53.618 --> 37:55.586
I have to go in.

38:05.530 --> 38:06.997
I haven't
ridden double

38:07.065 --> 38:08.794
since I was
a little girl.

38:08.866 --> 38:11.994
And I've never
been serenaded.

38:13.638 --> 38:15.071
So...

38:15.139 --> 38:17.266
it was
a lovely evening.

38:19.344 --> 38:21.437
<i>Molto grazie.</i>

38:21.546 --> 38:23.104
Right?

38:30.622 --> 38:33.182
<i>Buona notte, Catherina.</i>

38:37.562 --> 38:39.029
I'm fine!

38:39.097 --> 38:42.032
He won't tell me
who did it.

38:42.100 --> 38:44.034
It was dark!

38:44.102 --> 38:48.539
I only know they
all wore Brut aftershave

38:48.573 --> 38:51.041
and reeked
of Lavoris.

38:51.109 --> 38:54.044
Why were you
there by yourself?

38:54.112 --> 38:57.172
I was just
walking.

38:59.117 --> 39:01.984
Well, what kind of car
did they drive?

39:02.053 --> 39:05.989
It was a Mercedes
convertible.

39:06.057 --> 39:08.992
Was it blue?

39:09.060 --> 39:10.220
Yes.

39:10.328 --> 39:13.422
I've seen that car.

39:13.531 --> 39:17.763
They want a fight,
we'll give them a fight.

39:17.835 --> 39:19.268
We rednecks are few.

39:19.337 --> 39:23.103
College paleface
students are many.

39:23.174 --> 39:24.664
I counsel peace.

39:24.776 --> 39:27.108
Come on. Let's go find
those bastards.

39:27.178 --> 39:29.009
I have to go
somewhere.

39:34.285 --> 39:36.219
You haven't pledged
any sorority?

39:36.287 --> 39:37.379
No.

39:37.488 --> 39:40.218
You should. Most frat guys
won't date dormies.

39:40.291 --> 39:41.724
I'm the exception.

39:41.793 --> 39:46.059
So, you're on
the swimming team, huh?

39:46.130 --> 39:47.757
Yep.

39:47.865 --> 39:49.025
Breaststroke.

39:51.636 --> 39:52.694
<i>♪ Loosen it up ♪</i>

39:55.807 --> 39:57.240
<i>♪ Loosen it up... ♪ ♪</i>

40:06.117 --> 40:07.550
Is that him?

40:07.618 --> 40:09.210
I guess.

40:14.292 --> 40:15.418
Who are they?

40:15.526 --> 40:16.959
A bunch of cutters.

40:17.028 --> 40:18.461
What are cutters?

40:18.529 --> 40:20.588
Townies.

40:25.236 --> 40:27.932
There it is.
There's his Mercedes.

40:28.005 --> 40:31.634
Mike, I don't think
we can go in there.

40:31.743 --> 40:34.303
Oh, yeah?
Watch this.

40:39.751 --> 40:41.013
Shit.

40:41.085 --> 40:43.519
<i>Uh, due cappaccino.</i>

40:43.588 --> 40:47.285
Oh, that's
the wrong guy.

41:01.939 --> 41:04.840
A bunch of cutter kids.

41:14.452 --> 41:15.885
There he is.

41:32.236 --> 41:33.168
Hi there.

41:33.237 --> 41:35.671
Would you like
to roll some balls?

41:44.115 --> 41:45.673
Come on, Cyril!

41:50.621 --> 41:52.714
I can't get it out.

41:55.693 --> 41:58.457
My finger's stuck.

42:04.836 --> 42:06.770
My papa,
he tells me,

42:06.838 --> 42:07.770
<i>"Figlio mio,</i>

42:07.839 --> 42:09.773
"we are fishermen
in our family

42:09.841 --> 42:13.572
"for as far back
as I can see.

42:13.644 --> 42:16.078
"You... you can do
what you want.

42:16.147 --> 42:17.637
"You go to America.

42:17.748 --> 42:20.546
Say hello
to the new world for me."

42:20.618 --> 42:22.108
My papa.

42:23.654 --> 42:25.588
It's nice you
miss your parents.

42:25.656 --> 42:27.521
<i>Certo,  I miss.</i>

42:27.592 --> 42:30.220
Just like you miss
your mama and papa.

42:30.328 --> 42:32.796
I... I don't miss them.

42:32.864 --> 42:36.800
I went as far as I could
to get away from them.

42:36.868 --> 42:38.301
They miss you.

42:38.369 --> 42:41.770
At home, they sit,
and they look at your photo,

42:41.806 --> 42:43.296
and they say,

42:43.407 --> 42:46.672
"Ah, how we miss
our Catherina,

42:46.744 --> 42:48.735
our bambina."

42:57.555 --> 42:59.523
You shouldn't smoke.

43:01.158 --> 43:03.126
What's your major?

43:03.194 --> 43:04.252
Sosh.

43:04.362 --> 43:06.762
Oh, sosh.
That's a nice major.

43:06.831 --> 43:08.765
Would you mind if I...

43:08.833 --> 43:11.063
What are you
cutters doing here?

43:12.837 --> 43:14.771
Did you get lost?

43:14.839 --> 43:16.431
No.

43:16.540 --> 43:19.031
Then why don't you
get lost now?

43:22.613 --> 43:23.671
Is that him?

43:26.083 --> 43:29.484
Uh... no.
No, I don't think it is.

43:31.122 --> 43:33.113
Let's get
out of here.

43:33.224 --> 43:34.350
Smart move, shorty.

44:20.638 --> 44:22.868
All right!
Break it up!

44:24.175 --> 44:25.767
Oh, shit.

44:28.312 --> 44:29.404
Break it up!

44:29.513 --> 44:30.980
We gotta go now.

44:31.082 --> 44:32.606
Come on.

44:37.088 --> 44:39.022
Cutters started it!

44:41.993 --> 44:44.928
Break it up, everybody.
Get out of there.

44:45.029 --> 44:46.394
Move it!
Let's go!

44:49.633 --> 44:52.625
Most of you will only spend
four years here,

44:52.737 --> 44:56.537
but to a lot of us,
Bloomington is our home.

44:56.607 --> 44:59.633
I don't like how you've
been behaving in my home.

44:59.744 --> 45:03.942
If you feel compelled to compete
with the kids from the town,

45:04.015 --> 45:06.643
you will do it in
a different arena.

45:06.751 --> 45:11.654
We're expanding this year's
Little 500 bicycle race

45:11.722 --> 45:14.384
to include
a team from the town.

45:14.492 --> 45:16.119
But they're not
good enough.

45:17.962 --> 45:22.331
I don't want to be
in the Little 500.

45:22.400 --> 45:24.391
Oh, Christ.

45:24.502 --> 45:27.437
I thought you'd jump
at the chance.

45:27.505 --> 45:31.464
I don't want to be seen
with all those college kids.

45:31.575 --> 45:33.509
That's the point!

45:33.577 --> 45:36.512
Don't you want to beat
those shitheads

45:36.580 --> 45:38.377
in front
of everybody?

45:38.482 --> 45:40.882
Doesn't it take four
to have a team?

45:40.951 --> 45:42.384
Well, we got four...

45:42.453 --> 45:44.387
I mean, don't we?

45:46.323 --> 45:49.292
We all enter,
Dave rides the whole thing,

45:49.360 --> 45:50.793
and we win!

45:50.861 --> 45:52.158
Yeah, yeah, yeah, sure.

45:52.263 --> 45:53.195
Uh...

45:53.264 --> 45:54.526
Iook, Mike.

45:54.632 --> 45:57.100
I'm going to be working
that day, O.K.?

45:57.201 --> 45:58.190
Working?

45:58.302 --> 46:01.135
Yeah, I'm getting a job.

46:01.205 --> 46:02.433
By yourself?

46:03.541 --> 46:06.009
Yeah!
I need the money.

46:06.077 --> 46:08.011
Thanks, Dave.
That's really great.

46:08.079 --> 46:09.740
You're a real pal!

46:09.847 --> 46:11.280
You won't be working

46:11.348 --> 46:13.145
the day of
the Italian race.

46:13.250 --> 46:17.277
The time comes
when we all have to go our own ways.

46:17.388 --> 46:19.856
You're a real adult,
aren't you?

46:19.924 --> 46:22.484
B-town boy grows up.

46:22.593 --> 46:24.993
It's going to happen
sometime.

46:25.029 --> 46:26.462
Oh, yeah.

46:26.530 --> 46:28.464
Is that what
Nancy says?

46:28.532 --> 46:30.659
Just leave her
out of this.

46:30.768 --> 46:33.703
Shut up, would you?
I wasn't talking to you.

46:33.771 --> 46:37.468
Hey, well,
I don't give a damn!

46:37.575 --> 46:40.009
You're not
the quarterback here, Mike!

46:40.044 --> 46:42.012
At least I was once!

46:42.046 --> 46:45.072
Which is better than being
a midget all my life!

46:45.182 --> 46:47.980
Cut it out!
Just cut it out!

46:56.660 --> 46:58.992
<i>Hey, bambino,
che cosa?</i>

46:59.063 --> 47:01.031
Just drop that Italian,
all right?

47:01.065 --> 47:03.499
I'm really sick
of that crap.

47:04.869 --> 47:07.599
Oh, shit!

47:07.705 --> 47:11.141
You're just afraid
of those college guys.

47:11.208 --> 47:13.699
And you're not,
right, Mike?

47:13.811 --> 47:15.745
The only thing
I'm afraid of

47:15.813 --> 47:18.281
is wasting my life
with you guys!

47:18.382 --> 47:20.441
I thought that was
the whole plan,

47:20.551 --> 47:23.452
that we were going
to waste our lives together.

48:03.928 --> 48:05.418
What's he doing?
That guy...

48:21.679 --> 48:23.476
Come on, Rod!

48:25.149 --> 48:26.810
Come on, Mike!

48:39.763 --> 48:41.230
Yay, Rod! Whoo!

48:41.298 --> 48:42.765
[Cheering]

48:48.239 --> 48:49.900
Come on, Rod!

48:51.775 --> 48:54.175
You can do it!
Come on, Mike!

49:18.502 --> 49:19.833
Yay, Rod!

49:27.878 --> 49:28.936
Uhh!

49:49.199 --> 49:50.257
Mike!

49:50.367 --> 49:52.028
Mike!

49:52.136 --> 49:53.262
Hold on, Mike!

50:13.057 --> 50:15.491
I tried calling her
to tell her,

50:15.559 --> 50:16.992
but I just couldn't.

50:17.061 --> 50:20.997
She's going to see you
in the 500, you know.

50:23.901 --> 50:26.335
You know,
if she really likes you,

50:26.403 --> 50:29.338
she just won't care.

50:30.908 --> 50:32.842
Hey, uh, Dave,
me and Nancy,

50:32.910 --> 50:34.844
we're going
to get married.

50:34.912 --> 50:37.847
Moocher, you're
Catholic, aren't you?

50:37.915 --> 50:38.813
Yeah.

50:38.916 --> 50:40.850
You ever go
to confession?

50:40.918 --> 50:42.351
Twice.

50:42.419 --> 50:44.353
Make you feel better?

50:44.421 --> 50:46.355
Once.

50:47.458 --> 50:48.584
[Bell Tolls]

50:55.432 --> 50:57.866
Hi. Sorry I'm late.

50:57.935 --> 50:59.368
You look nice.

50:59.436 --> 51:01.063
Your hair looks great.

51:03.407 --> 51:06.308
What do you think
they're going to ask us?

51:06.377 --> 51:09.312
Nothing we can't answer,
I suppose.

51:11.415 --> 51:14.509
Wonder if I have
to have a job to qualify.

51:14.618 --> 51:17.280
I don't think so.

51:17.388 --> 51:20.323
I think it's mostly
blood and relatives

51:20.391 --> 51:21.824
that they're
interested in.

51:21.892 --> 51:24.326
Great.
I got both of them.

51:24.395 --> 51:26.829
Oh, fudge!
You know what?

51:26.897 --> 51:28.330
No. What?

51:28.399 --> 51:30.833
I only brought $4.00.

51:30.901 --> 51:33.836
Oh, well, it's only 5.

51:33.904 --> 51:36.839
Tell you what.
We'll go Dutch.

51:36.907 --> 51:38.340
On a marriage license?

51:38.409 --> 51:39.876
Sure. Why not?

52:00.097 --> 52:02.691
[Horn Honks]

52:02.800 --> 52:04.097
Papa!

52:04.201 --> 52:05.190
Ciao, Papa!

52:08.472 --> 52:12.306
[Car Engine
Not Starting]

52:15.345 --> 52:16.778
Aw, damn.

52:16.847 --> 52:19.281
You know
what I did?

52:19.349 --> 52:22.785
I mistakenly
put premium gas in this baby.

52:22.853 --> 52:24.787
It hates
expensive gas.

52:24.855 --> 52:27.653
[Horn Honks]

52:35.899 --> 52:38.735
Ohhh... oh...

52:39.536 --> 52:41.663
I should've hit him.

52:41.738 --> 52:44.002
He'd be dead now.
No more worries.

52:44.074 --> 52:45.803
I'll talk
to him, dear.

52:45.876 --> 52:48.310
I'll tell him
to get a job

52:48.378 --> 52:50.243
or go to college.

52:50.314 --> 52:53.306
College? So he can thumb
his diploma at me?

52:53.383 --> 52:56.079
Dave never thumbed
anything at anybody.

52:56.153 --> 52:58.587
That's because he never
went to college.

52:58.655 --> 53:01.988
Besides, he's probably
too stupid to get in.

53:02.059 --> 53:04.152
Shhh!
He'll hear you.

53:04.228 --> 53:06.162
I don't care!
It's my house.

53:06.230 --> 53:08.858
Besides, he doesn't
speak English anyway.

53:08.932 --> 53:12.424
I'm sure he'll find
a job somewhere.

53:12.536 --> 53:15.096
He couldn't find a job
to save his life.

53:15.172 --> 53:16.639
He's worthless,
Evelyn.

53:16.707 --> 53:20.199
I die of shame
every time I see him.

53:20.277 --> 53:21.209
Goddamn...

53:21.278 --> 53:22.302
Shh!

53:22.379 --> 53:24.313
Lazy freeloader.

53:40.731 --> 53:42.323
[Honks Horn]

53:46.403 --> 53:47.665
Hi, Alvin!

53:47.738 --> 53:49.296
Look who's here!

53:50.741 --> 53:53.005
Looks like
the safety inspector.

53:53.076 --> 53:54.737
Or a union organizer.

53:54.811 --> 53:56.676
Duke, I thought
you'd retired.

53:56.747 --> 53:58.681
They won't
let me retire.

53:58.749 --> 53:59.841
Howdy, boys.

54:13.764 --> 54:16.494
We could sign you up
as an apprentice.

54:16.600 --> 54:17.862
Like hell you can!

54:17.935 --> 54:19.869
I'm only here
for a visit,

54:19.937 --> 54:22.497
but if I wanted
to start over again,

54:22.606 --> 54:25.507
I could pick up
right where I left off.

54:39.723 --> 54:40.985
How are you,
Russell?

54:41.058 --> 54:43.322
Hi, Ray. All right.
How are you?

54:43.393 --> 54:44.325
Pretty good.

54:57.908 --> 55:01.344
Mind if I drive in
a wedge?

55:01.411 --> 55:02.503
All right.

55:46.390 --> 55:48.153
Hey, how's your son?

55:48.225 --> 55:50.216
He's fine.
How 'bout yours?

55:52.696 --> 55:54.596
I'm just tired
of it, Evelyn.

55:54.698 --> 55:56.996
I'm tired
of worrying about him.

55:57.067 --> 56:00.935
Who'd ever hire
a guy like that?

56:01.004 --> 56:03.666
He's going to
wind up a bum...

56:03.740 --> 56:05.367
An Italian bum.

56:08.245 --> 56:11.214
Well, you could use
some help.

56:11.281 --> 56:14.273
What if you
gave him a job?

56:14.351 --> 56:17.013
I don't want him
selling used cars.

56:17.087 --> 56:18.611
Why not?

56:18.722 --> 56:21.156
It's good enough
for you.

56:21.224 --> 56:24.352
Who says
it's good enough for me?

56:24.428 --> 56:26.157
You do.

56:26.229 --> 56:28.629
Damn right
it's good enough for me,

56:28.732 --> 56:30.632
but I don't need
any help.

56:30.734 --> 56:33.328
He'd ruin me
if I hired him,

56:33.403 --> 56:34.927
a weirdo kid
like that.

56:38.475 --> 56:39.442
[Whistling]

56:39.543 --> 56:41.807
Hey! No whistling!

56:41.912 --> 56:44.847
You're supposed
to be a shag boy, so shag.

56:44.915 --> 56:47.941
If I wanted whistling,
I'd get a bird.

57:08.071 --> 57:09.766
How are you feeling?

57:09.873 --> 57:10.965
Tired, Papa.

57:11.074 --> 57:12.006
Exhausted?

57:12.075 --> 57:13.235
Yeah.

57:13.343 --> 57:17.211
Get used to it.
It's going to be more of the same.

57:17.280 --> 57:18.975
Let's go home.

57:20.550 --> 57:22.108
I have to train.

57:23.520 --> 57:25.488
The Italian race
is next week.

57:59.122 --> 58:00.680
[Horn Honks]

58:30.053 --> 58:32.521
Pop, can I have
this Saturday off?

58:32.622 --> 58:34.647
Hell, no.

58:34.758 --> 58:36.419
Just this once, Papa.

58:36.526 --> 58:39.586
The Italians
are coming Saturday.

58:39.696 --> 58:42.290
I don't care
if the Second Coming's coming.

58:43.500 --> 58:45.695
But I waited
so long.

58:45.769 --> 58:47.396
No!

58:47.504 --> 58:49.870
N-o-double-O. No!

58:52.042 --> 58:54.840
Uh-oh.
You stay out of this.

59:00.116 --> 59:02.516
Don't come in here
with that. It's sold.

59:02.619 --> 59:05.281
You said there was
a 90-day guarantee.

59:05.388 --> 59:06.946
Guarantee?
What guarantee?

59:07.057 --> 59:08.649
You gave me
your word.

59:08.758 --> 59:10.419
Have you got it
on paper?

59:10.527 --> 59:14.987
There was no paper,
but you gave me your word.

59:15.098 --> 59:17.566
Word? I don't remember
hearing any word.

59:17.634 --> 59:19.534
Get this car off my lot!

59:19.636 --> 59:21.729
We have to take it back.

59:22.806 --> 59:24.535
Who are you?

59:26.142 --> 59:28.076
We're poor,
but we're honest.

59:28.144 --> 59:30.078
All I want
is a refund.

59:30.146 --> 59:31.113
Refund?

59:31.214 --> 59:33.444
Refund?
Are you crazy?

59:33.550 --> 59:34.448
Refund?

59:34.551 --> 59:35.779
Refund?

59:35.886 --> 59:37.478
Refund?

59:37.587 --> 59:38.815
Refund?

59:38.922 --> 59:40.355
Easy. Easy.
Easy, Ray.

59:40.457 --> 59:41.947
Refund?

59:42.058 --> 59:43.650
Refund.

59:44.761 --> 59:45.887
Refund?

59:48.098 --> 59:49.725
I've ruined everything.

59:49.833 --> 59:51.858
He needed a rest anyway,

59:51.968 --> 59:54.596
and now he's getting it.

59:54.704 --> 59:56.638
I'm not going
to the race.

59:56.706 --> 59:59.937
I should be here
when Papa wakes up.

01:00:09.486 --> 01:00:10.817
Um...

01:00:10.921 --> 01:00:13.719
did I ever
show you this?

01:00:16.326 --> 01:00:18.920
It's a passport.

01:00:19.029 --> 01:00:20.929
It's quite cheap,
you know.

01:00:20.997 --> 01:00:22.225
A real bargain.

01:00:22.332 --> 01:00:24.800
I carry this with me
all the time.

01:00:24.868 --> 01:00:27.359
Someday, there'll be
a new girl at the A & P,

01:00:27.437 --> 01:00:29.166
and when I
cash a check,

01:00:29.272 --> 01:00:31.103
she'll ask
for identification,

01:00:31.207 --> 01:00:33.141
and I'll take out
my passport,

01:00:33.209 --> 01:00:34.699
and I'll say,

01:00:34.811 --> 01:00:35.835
" Here!"

01:00:38.014 --> 01:00:39.345
Oh, Mama.

01:00:44.587 --> 01:00:46.452
So you see,

01:00:46.556 --> 01:00:48.524
I think
you really should go.

01:00:48.591 --> 01:00:51.253
I think
you should come home...

01:00:51.361 --> 01:00:52.555
singing...

01:00:52.662 --> 01:00:55.495
with a trophy.

01:00:55.598 --> 01:00:59.728
I think you should do
all those things while you can.

01:01:01.838 --> 01:01:04.807
I'll win this one
for you, Mama.

01:01:04.908 --> 01:01:06.136
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

01:01:06.242 --> 01:01:10.508
<i>welcome to today's
Cinzano 100-mile road race.</i>

01:01:10.613 --> 01:01:12.706
<i>Here they come
to the starting line...</i>

01:01:12.816 --> 01:01:14.807
<i>Team Cinzano,
ladies and gentlemen!</i>

01:01:25.528 --> 01:01:28.190
Timers,
if you are ready,

01:01:28.298 --> 01:01:30.391
we'll stand by
for the start

01:01:30.500 --> 01:01:31.899
of the Cinzano 100.

01:01:32.002 --> 01:01:34.095
Riders, ready!

01:01:34.204 --> 01:01:35.933
Timers, ready!

01:01:41.544 --> 01:01:44.980
<i>The Cinzano 100 is underway,
ladies and gentlemen.</i>

01:01:53.056 --> 01:01:56.355
<i>The riders are starting off
on a 100-mile journey.</i>

01:02:06.136 --> 01:02:07.603
Come on!

01:03:36.659 --> 01:03:38.126
Hey!

01:03:53.443 --> 01:03:54.967
Hey!

01:04:37.086 --> 01:04:38.553
<i>Buon giorno!</i>

01:04:40.056 --> 01:04:41.216
<i>Come'sta?</i>

01:04:44.894 --> 01:04:48.762
<i>Oggi e molto umido,
non e vero?</i>

01:04:48.865 --> 01:04:50.059
<i>Niento vero.</i>

01:05:01.844 --> 01:05:04.074
<i>Grazie! Grazie!</i>

01:05:04.147 --> 01:05:05.136
<i>Grazie!</i>

01:06:04.107 --> 01:06:07.599
<i>Che tempo
fara piovera!</i>

01:06:07.710 --> 01:06:08.734
<i>Filare!</i>

01:06:34.771 --> 01:06:36.398
Bravo! Bravo!

01:06:59.028 --> 01:07:02.156
I feel like one
of those dwarfs,

01:07:02.231 --> 01:07:05.257
like, when they think
that Snow White's dead.

01:07:09.505 --> 01:07:11.973
Well, I guess you're
a cutter again, huh?

01:07:12.041 --> 01:07:14.066
Just like the rest of us?

01:07:16.079 --> 01:07:18.172
I guess so.

01:07:24.487 --> 01:07:25.715
Hey, cheer up, Dave.

01:07:25.788 --> 01:07:27.722
You still got the 500.

01:07:32.295 --> 01:07:33.489
Thanks a lot.

01:07:38.368 --> 01:07:40.802
No, I don't feel lucky
to be alive.

01:07:40.870 --> 01:07:42.804
I feel lucky
I'm not dead.

01:07:42.872 --> 01:07:44.305
There's a difference.

01:07:46.275 --> 01:07:49.574
Oh! What
happened to you?

01:07:50.880 --> 01:07:52.313
Oh, it's nothing, Ma.

01:07:52.382 --> 01:07:55.613
How do you feel, Dad?

01:07:55.685 --> 01:07:57.050
" Dad"?

01:07:58.154 --> 01:08:01.749
I'll tell you how
I'm feeling, son.

01:08:01.824 --> 01:08:04.292
I had nightmares
all night

01:08:04.360 --> 01:08:07.158
that every customer
I ever had

01:08:07.230 --> 01:08:09.323
came in to ask
for a refund.

01:08:09.432 --> 01:08:11.400
You were there
handing out checks.

01:08:11.467 --> 01:08:13.765
"One for you,
one for you..."

01:08:13.836 --> 01:08:16.999
I'm sorry I gave him
back his money.

01:08:17.073 --> 01:08:19.200
I really am.

01:08:21.978 --> 01:08:23.877
Everybody cheats.

01:08:25.680 --> 01:08:27.876
I just didn't know.

01:08:29.986 --> 01:08:31.749
Well, now you know.

01:08:36.725 --> 01:08:38.091
Where's your trophy?

01:08:42.598 --> 01:08:43.564
Daddy!

01:08:45.635 --> 01:08:47.363
What's the matter?

01:08:47.437 --> 01:08:49.371
What are you
crying for?

01:08:49.439 --> 01:08:51.872
It's not like you
lost your wallet.

01:08:51.941 --> 01:08:54.375
I didn't want you
to be this miserable.

01:08:54.444 --> 01:08:58.038
A little bit's
all I asked for.

01:08:59.782 --> 01:09:01.305
Come on now.

01:09:05.720 --> 01:09:07.654
Talk to him, Evelyn.

01:09:09.459 --> 01:09:11.484
What are you doing?

01:09:22.104 --> 01:09:24.470
Hi, Kathy.

01:09:24.540 --> 01:09:26.837
What did you do
to yourself?

01:09:26.908 --> 01:09:28.843
Oh, I liked you
better before.

01:09:28.911 --> 01:09:31.402
<i>What happened
to your cornocello?</i>

01:09:34.617 --> 01:09:37.551
Now you look like
everybody else.

01:09:37.620 --> 01:09:39.484
I am everybody else.

01:09:39.555 --> 01:09:40.988
I mean...

01:09:41.057 --> 01:09:42.615
Listen, Kathy...

01:09:42.692 --> 01:09:43.783
Catherina!

01:09:47.863 --> 01:09:50.024
I feel terrible.

01:09:51.501 --> 01:09:53.696
You sound funny.

01:09:55.204 --> 01:09:56.637
<i>Che cosa, Enrico?</i>

01:10:00.710 --> 01:10:02.143
Tell me.

01:10:04.714 --> 01:10:06.045
Look...

01:10:06.115 --> 01:10:07.548
Kathy, I...

01:10:07.617 --> 01:10:08.982
My name is
Dave Stohler.

01:10:09.051 --> 01:10:12.282
I made all
that other stuff up.

01:10:12.355 --> 01:10:14.220
I was born in Bloomington.

01:10:14.290 --> 01:10:16.724
I went to
Bloomington high.

01:10:16.792 --> 01:10:20.228
I was treasurer
of the Latin Club...

01:10:20.296 --> 01:10:21.729
Stop kidding
around.

01:10:21.797 --> 01:10:23.731
I'm not
kidding around!

01:10:27.737 --> 01:10:28.829
See...

01:10:31.374 --> 01:10:34.468
I'm what you
call a cutter.

01:10:39.682 --> 01:10:41.115
Oh, and Napoli?

01:10:43.019 --> 01:10:44.953
And the
big family?

01:10:49.659 --> 01:10:53.117
Well, it was
a good act.

01:10:53.195 --> 01:10:54.787
You...

01:10:54.864 --> 01:10:57.094
You certainly
fooled me.

01:11:08.210 --> 01:11:10.644
You know
what you are?

01:11:10.713 --> 01:11:12.647
I got a clue.

01:11:12.715 --> 01:11:15.650
I'll tell you
what you are.

01:11:22.391 --> 01:11:24.484
Oh, God!

01:11:24.560 --> 01:11:25.492
You...

01:11:51.253 --> 01:11:52.413
Dave.

01:11:54.690 --> 01:11:55.918
Yes, Dad?

01:12:03.199 --> 01:12:06.134
I cut the stone
for this building.

01:12:06.202 --> 01:12:08.136
You did?

01:12:08.204 --> 01:12:11.640
Yeah. I was one
fine stonecutter.

01:12:11.707 --> 01:12:14.938
Mike's dad,
Moocher's, Cyril's...

01:12:15.011 --> 01:12:16.638
all of us.

01:12:18.180 --> 01:12:20.080
Well, Cyril's dad...

01:12:20.149 --> 01:12:21.138
never mind.

01:12:25.721 --> 01:12:29.157
Thing of it was,
I loved it.

01:12:30.726 --> 01:12:35.322
I was young
and slim and strong.

01:12:35.398 --> 01:12:38.834
I was damn
proud of my work.

01:12:38.901 --> 01:12:41.335
And the buildings
went up.

01:12:44.740 --> 01:12:48.676
When they were finished,
the damnedest thing happened.

01:12:50.079 --> 01:12:51.512
It was like...

01:12:51.580 --> 01:12:55.016
the buildings
was too good for us.

01:12:55.084 --> 01:12:57.018
Nobody told us that.

01:12:58.254 --> 01:12:59.346
Just...

01:13:00.923 --> 01:13:03.357
Just felt uncomfortable,
that's all.

01:13:05.594 --> 01:13:07.027
Even now, I...

01:13:07.096 --> 01:13:11.533
I'd like to be able
to stroll through the campus

01:13:11.600 --> 01:13:14.034
and look
at the limestone,

01:13:14.103 --> 01:13:17.539
but I just feel
out of place.

01:13:20.276 --> 01:13:23.712
You guys still go swimming
in the quarries?

01:13:23.779 --> 01:13:24.871
Sure.

01:13:25.948 --> 01:13:28.382
All you got to show

01:13:28.451 --> 01:13:31.386
for my 20 years of work

01:13:31.454 --> 01:13:34.389
is the holes
we left behind.

01:13:35.791 --> 01:13:37.725
I don't mind.

01:13:39.395 --> 01:13:41.488
I do.

01:13:41.564 --> 01:13:47.002
Cyril's dad says he took
that college exam.

01:13:47.069 --> 01:13:49.663
We both took it.

01:13:49.739 --> 01:13:52.674
How did
both of us do?

01:13:53.743 --> 01:13:55.677
Well,
I don't know.

01:13:57.113 --> 01:14:00.082
One of us
did O.K.

01:14:00.149 --> 01:14:02.310
But neither...

01:14:02.384 --> 01:14:03.316
of us...

01:14:03.385 --> 01:14:04.352
Hell, I...

01:14:04.420 --> 01:14:08.220
don't want to go
to college, Dad!

01:14:08.290 --> 01:14:10.224
To hell with them!

01:14:10.292 --> 01:14:12.783
I'm proud
of being a cutter.

01:14:14.296 --> 01:14:16.230
You're not a cutter.

01:14:16.298 --> 01:14:17.731
I'm a cutter.

01:14:19.135 --> 01:14:21.035
What,
are you afraid?

01:14:22.304 --> 01:14:23.396
Yeah.

01:14:24.607 --> 01:14:26.040
A little bit.

01:14:28.744 --> 01:14:32.578
And then there's
the rest of the guys.

01:14:37.586 --> 01:14:40.851
Well, you
took the exam.

01:14:40.923 --> 01:14:43.357
Did all right,
didn't you?

01:14:45.928 --> 01:14:47.520
Yes.

01:14:47.596 --> 01:14:49.029
Well, that's...

01:14:50.099 --> 01:14:51.532
That's good.

01:14:53.435 --> 01:14:54.868
Well, your mom...

01:14:58.941 --> 01:15:02.377
Your mom will be
expecting us home.

01:15:09.118 --> 01:15:10.551
Come on.

01:15:22.298 --> 01:15:24.664
I'm supposed to
ride this thing?

01:15:24.733 --> 01:15:26.667
Well, that's
the official issue.

01:15:26.735 --> 01:15:28.669
You can't add or
change anything.

01:15:28.737 --> 01:15:32.833
Well, it's a
piece of junk!

01:15:32.908 --> 01:15:36.674
Hey, it's got a lot
of personality to it.

01:15:36.745 --> 01:15:39.680
It doesn't look
that bad to me.

01:15:39.748 --> 01:15:42.683
That's 'cause
you don't have to ride it.

01:15:44.753 --> 01:15:46.345
You don't have to ride.

01:15:46.422 --> 01:15:48.356
We're not going to beg you.

01:15:48.424 --> 01:15:50.756
We'll plead,
but never beg.

01:15:50.826 --> 01:15:52.851
The hell with it!

01:15:52.928 --> 01:15:54.361
Get off, Cyril.

01:15:54.430 --> 01:15:56.796
At least
we got invited.

01:15:59.268 --> 01:16:02.032
I'll just
take it back.

01:16:02.104 --> 01:16:04.538
You seem
relieved, Mike.

01:16:04.607 --> 01:16:08.099
Don't you think
we can win anymore?

01:16:10.546 --> 01:16:12.878
Why not?

01:16:12.948 --> 01:16:16.406
<i>Maybe those guys
are better than us.</i>

01:16:18.787 --> 01:16:22.780
That's the first
time you ever said that!

01:16:22.858 --> 01:16:27.124
That's the first time
I ever felt that.

01:16:32.134 --> 01:16:33.567
All right.

01:18:18.707 --> 01:18:20.174
Hello.

01:18:23.812 --> 01:18:25.746
What are you
doing here?

01:18:27.816 --> 01:18:29.477
I'm leaving soon.

01:18:30.886 --> 01:18:32.683
Where are you going?

01:18:32.755 --> 01:18:34.882
I got a job
in Chicago.

01:18:34.957 --> 01:18:37.391
Moocher's dad got
a job in Chicago.

01:18:37.459 --> 01:18:38.323
He's, uh...

01:18:43.966 --> 01:18:49.063
I'm going to Italy
after all with my parents.

01:18:49.138 --> 01:18:50.901
Great, Kath.

01:18:50.973 --> 01:18:53.908
I wish you
a nice trip.

01:18:53.976 --> 01:18:55.500
You, too.

01:18:55.577 --> 01:18:57.511
I'm not going
anywhere.

01:18:59.815 --> 01:19:02.477
I don't know
about that.

01:19:10.059 --> 01:19:10.991
Thank you.

01:19:11.060 --> 01:19:12.152
You're welcome.

01:19:12.227 --> 01:19:16.163
If you eat so much,
how come you're small?

01:19:16.231 --> 01:19:17.664
Oh, it's my
metabolism.

01:19:17.733 --> 01:19:20.327
I eat three
times a day.

01:19:20.402 --> 01:19:23.337
My metabolism
eats five times a day.

01:19:24.406 --> 01:19:26.840
Well, I go back
to work tomorrow.

01:19:26.909 --> 01:19:28.843
You won't
watch us race?

01:19:28.911 --> 01:19:31.846
He thought he might
bring you bad luck.

01:19:31.914 --> 01:19:35.179
Well, I just have
work to do, that's all.

01:19:35.250 --> 01:19:39.778
Besides, there might be
another metabolism to feed here.

01:19:39.855 --> 01:19:41.914
We might be
a father?

01:19:41.990 --> 01:19:44.788
<i>No, I might be a father.
Your mom might be a mother.</i>

01:19:44.860 --> 01:19:47.124
You might be a brother.

01:19:47.196 --> 01:19:50.723
That way, I keep it
all in the family.

01:19:50.799 --> 01:19:53.859
I didn't think
people your age...

01:19:53.936 --> 01:19:57.633
The next word
may be your last.

01:19:57.706 --> 01:20:00.197
You must
be very happy.

01:20:00.275 --> 01:20:02.869
Do I have
any choice?

01:20:02.945 --> 01:20:06.813
You were going
to give a pep talk.

01:20:06.882 --> 01:20:08.816
They don't need pep.

01:20:08.884 --> 01:20:10.317
I need pep.

01:20:10.385 --> 01:20:13.320
Go on,
give it to them.

01:20:20.729 --> 01:20:22.162
Uh, we thought...

01:20:22.231 --> 01:20:24.165
As long as
you're out there,

01:20:24.233 --> 01:20:27.327
you might as well
tell them who you are.

01:20:27.402 --> 01:20:28.494
Right.

01:20:30.072 --> 01:20:33.166
Oh, wow!

01:20:33.275 --> 01:20:37.302
<i>♪ Oh, say,
can you see ♪</i>

01:20:37.379 --> 01:20:42.112
<i>♪ By the dawn's
early light ♪</i>

01:20:42.184 --> 01:20:46.450
<i>♪ What so proudly
we hailed ♪</i>

01:20:46.522 --> 01:20:51.118
<i>♪ At the twilight's
last gleaming? ♪</i>

01:20:51.193 --> 01:20:55.289
<i>♪ Whose broad stripes
and bright stars ♪</i>

01:20:55.364 --> 01:21:00.427
<i>♪ Through the
perilous fight ♪</i>

01:21:00.502 --> 01:21:04.370
<i>♪ O'er the ramparts
we watched ♪</i>

01:21:04.439 --> 01:21:09.172
<i>♪ Were so gallantly
streaming ♪</i>

01:21:09.244 --> 01:21:13.772
<i>♪ And the rocket's
red glare ♪</i>

01:21:13.849 --> 01:21:18.411
<i>♪ The bombs bursting
in air ♪</i>

01:21:18.487 --> 01:21:23.083
<i>♪ Gave proof
through the night ♪</i>

01:21:23.158 --> 01:21:27.822
<i>♪ That our flag
was still there ♪</i>

01:21:27.896 --> 01:21:30.888
<i>♪ Oh, say, does that ♪</i>

01:21:30.966 --> 01:21:34.925
<i>♪ Star-spangled banner ♪</i>

01:21:35.003 --> 01:21:39.303
<i>♪ Yet wave ♪</i>

01:21:39.374 --> 01:21:45.313
<i>♪ O'er the land
of the free ♪</i>

01:21:45.380 --> 01:21:53.151
<i>♪ And the home
of the brave ♪ ♪</i>

01:22:00.162 --> 01:22:02.960
Gentlemen,
thank you very much.

01:22:03.031 --> 01:22:08.435
I want to point out three flags
you'll have to obey.

01:22:08.503 --> 01:22:12.940
First, the green flag
means the race is on.

01:22:13.008 --> 01:22:16.444
The green flag means
you are racing.

01:22:16.511 --> 01:22:20.311
The yellow flag means
there's been an accident

01:22:20.382 --> 01:22:26.287
or someone has a problem
that will slow down the track.

01:22:26.355 --> 01:22:28.289
Please follow
your leader.

01:22:28.357 --> 01:22:33.522
The third flag is
the checkered flag.

01:22:33.595 --> 01:22:35.825
This needs
no explanation.

01:22:49.144 --> 01:22:54.673
This is a 200-lap,
50-mile bicycle race.

01:22:56.485 --> 01:23:00.251
It will consist of 33
4-man teams.

01:23:00.322 --> 01:23:02.256
For the first year,

01:23:02.324 --> 01:23:07.387
an out-of-town team has
been invited to participate.

01:23:07.462 --> 01:23:11.762
I'm sure they'll give
their best effort.

01:23:11.833 --> 01:23:14.267
The Cutters,
ladies and gentlemen.

01:23:15.570 --> 01:23:21.270
Any team members may exchange
to another team member

01:23:21.343 --> 01:23:25.575
whenever they feel exhausted
or in need of help.

01:23:27.249 --> 01:23:28.477
Gentlemen...

01:23:30.319 --> 01:23:33.686
mount your
Roadmaster bicycle.

01:23:33.755 --> 01:23:35.689
