I.U.!

01:24:41.690 --> 01:24:44.124
They're on
the starting line.

01:24:44.192 --> 01:24:47.958
They're coming down!
The green flag is up!

01:24:48.029 --> 01:24:51.521
The Little 500
is underway!

01:25:18.894 --> 01:25:21.829
And here they come,
rounding the corner

01:25:21.897 --> 01:25:26.061
for the completion of
the first of 200 laps today.

01:25:56.565 --> 01:25:57.998
<i>So after 25 laps,</i>

01:25:58.066 --> 01:26:00.000
<i>two of the perennial
favorites</i>

01:26:00.068 --> 01:26:01.501
<i>are up front...</i>

01:26:01.570 --> 01:26:04.004
<i>The Sigma Tau Omega team
and the Acacia team.</i>

01:26:04.072 --> 01:26:05.505
<i>I should point out</i>

01:26:05.574 --> 01:26:08.008
<i>what a remarkable job
the Cutter team is doing.</i>

01:26:08.076 --> 01:26:10.010
<i>They started in
34th position</i>

01:26:10.078 --> 01:26:12.672
<i>and are moving up
through the field.</i>

01:26:12.747 --> 01:26:13.941
Oh...

01:26:15.417 --> 01:26:19.513
<i>The Acacia team just signaled
for an exchange.</i>

01:26:19.588 --> 01:26:22.887
<i>The single rider is
accelerating away,</i>

01:26:22.958 --> 01:26:26.359
<i>getting a lead
so the receiver</i>

01:26:26.428 --> 01:26:30.159
<i>will not be behind
when the pack comes by.</i>

01:26:30.232 --> 01:26:31.529
<i>Beautiful exchange!</i>

01:26:31.600 --> 01:26:34.034
<i>The other team is exchanging
right behind them.</i>

01:26:35.837 --> 01:26:37.270
<i>Sigma Tau Omega team.</i>

01:26:39.040 --> 01:26:41.975
<i>Another team is moving in
on the outside.</i>

01:26:42.043 --> 01:26:44.913
<i>It's team 34,
the Cutter team.</i>

01:26:45.046 --> 01:26:47.981
<i>He is fighting hard
to take the lead.</i>

01:26:48.049 --> 01:26:50.483
<i>He has taken the lead!</i>

01:26:50.552 --> 01:26:52.986
<i>Team 34 has succeeded</i>

01:26:53.054 --> 01:26:55.488
<i>in taking the lead
from the last position.</i>

01:26:55.557 --> 01:26:58.492
<i>What an incredible effort
by the leader of this race.</i>

01:26:58.560 --> 01:27:00.494
Come on!
You got him!

01:27:28.356 --> 01:27:29.789
<i>The Delta Chis</i>

01:27:29.858 --> 01:27:31.291
<i>and the Acacia team.</i>

01:27:31.359 --> 01:27:33.793
<i>The rider for
the Cutters team...</i>

01:27:33.862 --> 01:27:34.794
<i>Dave Stohler...</i>

01:27:34.863 --> 01:27:36.296
That's my boy!

01:27:36.364 --> 01:27:38.229
<i>is pulling
ahead even further...</i>

01:27:38.300 --> 01:27:40.359
Pulling ahead!

01:27:40.435 --> 01:27:42.266
<i>It's incredible
what he's...</i>

01:27:42.337 --> 01:27:43.861
Come on, Dave!

01:27:43.939 --> 01:27:47.875
<i>He's turning in
some terrific
lap times here.</i>

01:27:47.943 --> 01:27:51.003
<i>I don't happen to have
a stopwatch, but...</i>

01:27:59.654 --> 01:28:01.019
He won't last.

01:28:02.991 --> 01:28:04.424
<i>It's utterly amazing.</i>

01:28:04.492 --> 01:28:08.861
<i>After 25 miles...
that's 100 laps, folks...</i>

01:28:08.930 --> 01:28:11.990
the rider for the Cutters
is still out front.

01:28:12.067 --> 01:28:15.400
<i>He has yet to
come in for an exchange.</i>

01:28:18.273 --> 01:28:19.968
We're
number one!

01:28:27.315 --> 01:28:30.011
<i>Someone's down.
There's an accident.</i>

01:28:30.085 --> 01:28:31.416
<i>I can't see who.</i>

01:28:31.486 --> 01:28:32.919
<i>Just a second.</i>

01:28:32.988 --> 01:28:36.424
<i>It's Dave Stohler
from the Cutter team.</i>

01:28:36.491 --> 01:28:39.358
<i>He had a 3/4-lap lead.</i>

01:28:39.427 --> 01:28:42.191
<i>I can't see
if he's hurt.</i>

01:28:42.263 --> 01:28:45.027
<i>He's getting back
on the bike,</i>

01:28:45.100 --> 01:28:47.534
<i>but he's obviously
in agony.</i>

01:28:48.937 --> 01:28:50.370
Come on, Dave!

01:28:50.438 --> 01:28:52.372
No way.
He wants off, man.

01:28:52.440 --> 01:28:53.873
That's the signal.

01:28:53.942 --> 01:28:55.466
He's coming in.

01:28:59.247 --> 01:29:00.612
Here you go.

01:29:00.682 --> 01:29:03.674
I don't want
to race.

01:29:09.357 --> 01:29:11.552
Get on the bike!

01:29:11.626 --> 01:29:14.561
It's ours now.
It's our race.

01:29:14.629 --> 01:29:16.119
We got it.

01:29:16.197 --> 01:29:17.926
Get going!

01:29:17.999 --> 01:29:19.432
No one is going.

01:29:19.501 --> 01:29:21.867
The other riders
are holding the bike.

01:29:21.936 --> 01:29:23.961
Get out there,
Mike!

01:29:24.039 --> 01:29:26.064
Get on the bike!

01:29:26.141 --> 01:29:27.608
The little
guy's riding!

01:29:32.380 --> 01:29:33.813
- You O.K.?
- What's the matter?

01:29:33.882 --> 01:29:34.814
What
happened?

01:29:39.421 --> 01:29:42.788
<i>As a result of that
terrible exchange,</i>

01:29:42.857 --> 01:29:46.088
<i>the Cutter team has
dropped from the lead.</i>

01:29:46.161 --> 01:29:48.857
<i>The Sigma Tau Omega team
has regained the lead.</i>

01:29:48.930 --> 01:29:53.094
<i>The Cutter team has fallen
into second position.</i>

01:29:55.003 --> 01:29:58.439
<i>Another team has passed
the Cutter team.</i>

01:29:58.506 --> 01:30:01.441
<i>The Cutters
are in third place</i>

01:30:01.509 --> 01:30:04.307
<i>and seem to be
losing ground.</i>

01:30:13.688 --> 01:30:15.121
Well, Ev, he tried.

01:30:15.190 --> 01:30:18.125
Even the announcer
said he tried.

01:30:47.822 --> 01:30:49.255
It's all over.

01:31:02.237 --> 01:31:03.534
Help!

01:31:17.919 --> 01:31:19.511
Nice try, kid.

01:31:19.587 --> 01:31:24.183
<i>The lead team has just
completed 170 laps.</i>

01:31:24.259 --> 01:31:26.284
<i>There are 30 laps
remaining.</i>

01:31:26.361 --> 01:31:28.795
<i>Sigma Tau Omega
looks unbeatable.</i>

01:31:28.863 --> 01:31:32.196
<i>Many things can happen,
as we've already seen.</i>

01:31:32.267 --> 01:31:35.202
<i>Things can change
like the wind.</i>

01:31:35.270 --> 01:31:37.738
Stay on
this side.

01:31:40.208 --> 01:31:41.641
Bring it in!

01:31:50.618 --> 01:31:53.178
Go, you Cutter, go!

01:32:05.166 --> 01:32:09.262
<i>The Cutters now have
a new man on the bike.</i>

01:32:09.337 --> 01:32:12.363
<i>He's doing a good job.</i>

01:32:12.440 --> 01:32:16.206
<i>He has moved the Cutters
into fourth position.</i>

01:32:16.277 --> 01:32:20.543
<i>He might make a serious
challenge for third position.</i>

01:32:20.615 --> 01:32:23.948
<i>We'll wait to see
if this happens.</i>

01:32:24.018 --> 01:32:26.919
We're not
doing too bad.

01:32:29.958 --> 01:32:32.449
<i>This once again points out</i>

01:32:32.527 --> 01:32:35.325
<i>the fact that this
is a team effort.</i>

01:32:35.396 --> 01:32:39.833
<i>One man may fall back,
another may be exceptional...</i>

01:32:58.386 --> 01:33:00.047
We showed them.

01:33:00.121 --> 01:33:01.554
Showed them what?

01:33:04.792 --> 01:33:07.886
Come on, Mike!
Bring it in!

01:33:07.962 --> 01:33:09.429
Come on!

01:33:22.210 --> 01:33:24.405
<i>Stohler is on the bike,</i>

01:33:24.479 --> 01:33:28.916
<i>his teammates are taping
his feet to the pedals.</i>

01:33:28.983 --> 01:33:33.420
<i>This means he won't be able
to exchange riders.</i>

01:33:33.488 --> 01:33:37.083
<i>He must ride
15 laps by himself.</i>

01:33:37.158 --> 01:33:38.523
Pick it up!

01:33:38.593 --> 01:33:40.527
Pick it up!

